{{en-noun}}

# A place for the [[detention]] of [[stray]] or [[wander]]ing [[animal]]s.
#: {{syn|en|animal shelter}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=N. R. Kleinfield|title=Robert Sarnoff, 78, RCA Chairman, Dies|work=The New York Times|date=1997-02-24|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/02/24/nyregion/robert-sarnoff-78-rca-chairman-dies.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Mr. Sarnoff also sent to the '''pound''' one of the best-known dogs in the world. Nipper, the black-and-white terrier usually depicted peering with head cocked into the horn of a Victrola, listening for “His Master's Voice,” was de-emphasized as a corporate symbol.}}
# {{lb|en|metonymy}} The people who work for the pound.
