====Verb====
{{en-verb|~s|~ing|~d}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To hit in the face with a pie, either for comic effect or as a means of protest (see also [[pieing]]).
#: {{ux|en|I'd like to see someone '''pie''' the chairman of the board.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To go around (a corner) in a guarded manner.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} (of printing types) To reduce to confusion; to jumble.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1943|author=Esther Forbes Hoskins|title=[[wikipedia:Johnny Tremain|Johnny Tremain]]|passage=The door of the [printing] shop was shattered. He went in. The presses were broken. The type pied.}}

