==Norwegian Bokmål==
{{wikipedia|lang=nb}}

[[Image:Latin letter A.svg|250px|thumb|The [[letter]]  '''''A''''' from the [[Norwegian]] alphabet.]]

===Etymology===
From {{der|nb|la|A}}, from {{der|nb|grc|Α|t=alpha}}, likely through the {{der|nb|ett|-}} language, from {{der|nb|phn|𐤀}}, from Proto-Canaanite [[Image:Protoalef.svg|20px]], from Proto-Sinaitic [[Image:Proto-semiticA-01.svg|20px]], from {{der|nb|egy|𓃾}} representing the head of an [[ox]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|nb|/ɑː/}}
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|nb|/ɑː/|/a/}}
* {{audio|nb|Pronunciation of Norwegian Bokmål «A», «a».ogg|Audio}}
* {{hyphenation|nb|A}}
* {{homophones|nb|a|à|A-|a-|ah}}

===Letter===
{{head|nb|letter|upper case||lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def|nb|letter|1}}

====See also====
* {{list:Latin script letters/nb/simple}}

===Noun===
{{nb-noun-m1|A-}}

# the letter {{l|en|A}}
# {{lb|en|horology}} symbol for {{l|en|avance}}
# {{lb|en|physics}} symbol for {{l|en|ampere}}
# {{lb|en|physics}} symbol for {{l|en|nucleon number}}

