==Middle English==

===Noun===
{{head|enm|noun}}

# {{alternative form of|enm|crowe}}

{{shortcut|AP:ENPRON}}
==English==
The following tables show the [[Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet|International Phonetic Alphabet]] (IPA) and the English pronunciation (enPR) or {{w|American Heritage Dictionary}} (AHD) symbols that are used to represent the various sounds of the {{w|English language}}. The sounds of [[Received Pronunciation]] (RP, UK), [[General American]] pronunciation (GenAm, US), Canadian English (CanE), Australian English (AuE){{,}} and New Zealand English (NZE) are shown.

For vowels in other dialects, see Wikipedia's {{w|IPA chart for English}}.

:''An [[:Image:IPA Chart for English 2.png|image of an old version of these tables]] is available.''

===[[vowel|Vowels]]===
For a fuller list of dialects, see {{w|International Phonetic Alphabet chart for English dialects}}.

Non-rhotic dialects (RP, Australia, New Zealand) do not pronounce what was historically a syllable-final ''r''; instead they have a schwa ({{IPAchar|/ə/}} or, in NZ, {{IPAchar|/ɘ/}}), centering diphthong (ending in {{IPAchar|/ə̯/}}){{,}} or a long vowel (ending in {{IPAfont|ː}}). In addition to pronouncing syllable-final ''r'', the rhotic dialects (General American and Canadian) do not have a vowel length distinction, so none of their vowels end in the length symbol {{IPAfont|ː}}.

This vowel table lists both [[monophthong]]s and [[diphthong]]s.

