| {{l|en|carry|c'''arr'''y}}, {{l|en|marry|m'''arr'''y}}, {{l|en|paragraph|p'''ar'''agraph}}<ref name="Mary-marry-merry">In many accents in the United States and most accents in Canada, some or all of the vowels of ''Mary'', ''marry''{{,}} and ''merry'' are merged (the [[w:Mary&ndash;marry&ndash;merry merger|''Mary''&ndash;''marry''&ndash;''merry'' merger]]). If all three are merged, the resulting vowel is usually transcribed {{IPAchar|/ɛɹ/}}. In accents that distinguish all three, ''marry'' has {{IPAchar|/æɹ/}}, ''merry'' has {{IPAchar|/ɛɹ/}}{{,}} and ''Mary'' has {{IPAchar|/eɹ/}}.</ref>
