{{also|Elephant|éléphant|êléphant}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|elefant}}, {{m|enm|elefaunt}}, from {{der|en|fro|elefant}}, {{m|fro|elefan}}, {{m|fro|olifant}}, re-latinized in {{der|en|frm|-}} as {{m|frm|elephant}}, from {{der|en|la|elephantus}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἐλέφᾱς}} (gen. {{m|grc|ἐλέφαντος}}). Believed to be derived from an {{der|en|afa|-}} form such as {{der|en|ber-pro|*eḷu||elephant}} (compare {{cog|thv|êlu}}, {{cog|taq|alu}}) or {{der|en|egy|ꜣbw||elephant; ivory}}. More at {{m|en|ivory}}. Replaced {{cog|enm|olifant}} (from the aforementioned {{w|Old French}} form, from {{cog|VL.|*olifantus}}), which replaced {{cog|ang|elpend|t=elephant}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈɛləfənt/|/ˈɛlɪfənt/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-elephant.ogg|Audio (US)}}
[[Image:Elephant near ndutu.jpg|thumb|an elephant]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# A [[mammal]] of the order [[Proboscidea]], having a [[trunk]], and two large [[ivory]] [[tusks]] jutting from the upper [[jaw]].
# {{lb|en|in particular}} Any member of the family [[Elephantidae]] that is not a [[mammoth]].
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Anything [[huge]] and [[ponderous]].
# {{lb|en|paper|printing}} {{synonym of|en|elephant paper}}
# {{lb|en|British|childish}} {{n-g|used when counting to add length, so that each count takes about one second}}
#: ''Let's play hide and seek. I'll count. One '''elephant''', two '''elephant''', three '''elephant'''...''
# {{lb|en|uncountable|obsolete}} [[ivory|Ivory]].
#* {{RQ:Dryden Aeneid}}
#*: He sent rich gifts of '''elephant''' and gold.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|animal}} ''[[Elephas]] [[maximus]]'', ''[[Loxodonta]] [[africana]]''
* {{sense|counting term}} see [[Appendix:Words used as placeholders to count seconds]]

====Hyponyms====
* {{sense|animal}} {{vern|African bush elephant}}, {{l|en|African forest elephant}}, {{l|en|Indian elephant}}, {{l|en|African elephant}}

