===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|December}}, {{m|enm|Decembre}}, from {{der|en|fro|decembre}}, from {{der|en|la|december|t=tenth month}}, from {{der|en|la|decem|t=ten}}; + {{der|en|la|-ber}}, from {{m|la|-bris}}, an adjectival suffix; December was the tenth month in the Roman calendar.

