==Danish==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|da|fr|marche}}, derived from the verb {{m|fr|marcher||to march}}, a Frankish loanword, ultimately from {{der|da|gem-pro|*markōną||to mark, notice}}. The interjection is borrowed form the French imperative of this verb.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|da|[ˈmɑːɕ]}}

===Noun===
{{da-noun|en|er}}

# {{l|en|march}}

===Interjection===
{{da-interj}}

# {{l|en|march}}! {{q|an order}}

----

