* {{audio|en|en-au-august.ogg|Audio (AU)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ʌst}}
* {{hyphenation|en|au|gust}}

===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₂ewg-}}
From {{der|en|fr|auguste||noble, stately; august}} or {{der|en|la|augustus||majestic, venerable, august; imperial, royal}},<ref>{{R:Lexico}}</ref> from {{m|la|augeō||to augment, increase; to enlarge, expand, spread}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂ewg-||to enlarge, increase}}. {{doublet|en|Augustus}}.

====Adjective====
{{en-adj|er|more}}

# [[awe-inspiring|Awe-inspiring]], [[majestic]], [[noble]], [[venerable]].
#: {{ux|en|an '''august''' patron of the arts}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Gilbert Bishop of Sarum [''i.e.'', {{w|Gilbert Burnet}}]|chapter=Article VII. Of the Old Testament.|title=An Exposition of the XXXIX Articles of the Church of England|location=Oxford|publisher=At the [[w:Oxford University Press|Clarendon Press]]|year=1796|page=123|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZygPAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA123|oclc=191672588|passage=In the [[w:Psalms|book of Pſalms]] there are many things ſaid of {{w|David}}, which ſeem capable of a much '''auguſter''' ſenſe than can be pretended to be anſwered by any thing that befel himſelf.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=William Sollis|title=A Sermon, Preached in Holsworthy Church on Thursday, August 31, 1837, at the Anniversaries of the Societies for Promoting Christian Knowledge, and for Propagating the Gospel in Foreign Parts.{{nb...|Published by Request of the Members then Present.}}|location=Launceston, Cornwall|publisher=Penheale-Press, Rev. H. A. Simcoe|date=31 August 1837|page=7|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=LedoAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA7|oclc=31888331|passage=[W]e shall not, I think, be able to find language which can convey in few words more fully the idea we should always have impressed on our minds of the '''august''' character of our Lord, than the expression, "the word of life."}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=E[lijah] C[oleman] Bridgman|authorlink=Elijah Coleman Bridgman|chapter=Governmental Affairs|title=A Chinese Chrestomathy in the Canton Dialect|location=Macao|publisher=[[w:Samuel Wells Williams|S[amuel] Wells Williams]]|year=1841|section=section second (Imperial Titles)|page=558|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=Yl9cAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA558|oclc=806406066|passage=The commands of the '''august''' sovereign are the imperial commands, or the phœnix (the incomparable) mandate.}}
