====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} Of an event, to write in a [[memo]] or the [[minutes]] of a meeting.
#: {{ux|en|I’ll '''minute''' this evening’s meeting.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|1870|Charles Dickens|Speeches Literary and Social|chapter=Administrative Reform|page=133|origdate=June 27, 1855|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bT5WAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA133|passage=I dare say there was a vast amount of '''minuting''', memoranduming, and despatch-boxing, on this mighty subject.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1995|author=Edmund Dell|title=The Schuman Plan and the British Abdication of Leadership in Europe|url=http://print.google.com/print?hl=en&id=us6DpQrcaVEC&pg=PA74&lpg=PA74&sig=8WYGZFKFxIhE4WPCpVkzDvHpO1A|passage=On 17 November 1949 Jay '''minuted''' Cripps, arguing that trade liberalization on inessentials was socially regressive.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1996|author=Peter Hinchliffe|title=The Other Battle|url=http://print.google.com/print?hl=en&id=vxBK8kHLTyIC&pg=PA78&lpg=PA78&sig=lXg1Kvn_f1KsmB4gdOv51h5nu8I|passage=The Commander-in-Chief of Bomber Command, Sir Richard Peirse, was sceptical of its findings, '''minuting,''' ‘I don’t think at this rate we could have hoped to produce the damage which is known to have been achieved.’}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2003|author=David Roberts|title=Four Against the Arctic|url=http://print.google.com/print?hl=en&id=yPsgKV7zo_kC&pg=PA18&lpg=PA18&sig=WNGXG6bM-ja8NDueqgtdNrCkslM|passage=Mr. Klingstadt, chief Auditor of the Admiralty of that city, sent for and examined them very particularly concerning the events which had befallen them; '''minuting''' down their answers in writing, with an intention of publishing himself an account of their extraordinary adventures.}}
# To set down a short sketch or note of; to jot down; to make a minute or a brief summary of.
#* {{quote-book|en|1876|George Bancroft|History of the United States from the discovery of the American continent|url=https://hdl.handle.net/2027/msu.31293006283612?urlappend=%3Bseq=52 |pages=28-29|volume=VI|origyear=1834|passage=The Empress of Russia, with her own hand, '''minuted''' an edict for universal tolerance.}}

