===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To [[engage]] in trade.
#: {{syn|en|deal}}
#: {{ux|en|This company '''trades''' (in) precious metal.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|1727|John Arbuthnot|Tables of Ancient Coins, Weights and Measures||248|{{...}}a free port, where Nations warring with one another resorted with their Goods, and '''traded''' as in a neutral Country.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UmBMAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA248}}
# {{lb|en|finance|intransitive|copulative}} To be traded at a certain price or under certain conditions.
#: {{ux|en|Apple is '''trading''' at $200.}}
#: {{ux|en|ExxonMobil '''trades''' on the NYSE.}}
#: {{ux|en|The stock is '''trading''' rich relative to its sector.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To give (something) in [[exchange]] for.
#: {{syn|en|exchange|swap|switch|truck|id4=trade}}
#: {{ux|en|Will you '''trade''' your precious watch for my earring?}}
# {{lb|en|gardening|transitive|or|intransitive}} To give someone a plant and receive a different one in return.
# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To do business; offer for sale as for one's [[livelihood]].
#: {{syn|en|do business}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To have dealings; to be concerned or associated (with).
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Macbeth|III|v|passage=Saucy and over bold, how did you dare / To '''trade''' and traffic with Macbeth}}

