==Galician==
{{wikipedia|lang=gl}}
[[Image:Auger 3 (PSF).png|thumb|upright|''Trado'' ("auger")]]

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|gl|trado}}

===Etymology===
From the medieval (Old Galician / {{inh|gl|roa-opt|-}}) form {{m|roa-opt|traado}} (13th century), from {{inh|gl|LL.|taratrum|t=auger}}, attested by {{w|Isidore of Seville}}. Either from {{der|gl|qfa-sub-ibe|-}} or from {{der|gl|cel-gau|-}}, from {{der|gl|cel-pro|*taratrom}}, from {{der|gl|ine-pro|*terh₁-|*térh₁-tro-}}.<ref>{{R:DCECH|taladro}}</ref><ref>{{R:Matasovic 2009|370}}</ref> Cognate with {{cog|pt|trado}}, {{cog|es|taladro}}, {{cog|sga|tarathar}}, {{cog|owl|tarater}}, {{cog|br|tarar}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gl|/ˈtɾaðe̝/}}

===Noun===
{{gl-noun|m}}

# [[auger]]
#* '''1448''', X. Ferro Couselo (ed.), ''A vida e a fala dos devanceiros''. Vigo: Galaxia, page 295:
#*: ''quatro '''traados''' et hua segur et hua aixola montisca''
#*:: four '''augers''' and a hatchet and an adze

