{{topics|vep|Parts of speech}}

{{also|adjectivé}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fro|adjectif}}, from {{der|en|la|adiectivus}}, from {{m|la|adiciō}} + {{m|la|-īvus}}, from {{m|la|ad-||to, towards, at}} + {{m|la|iaciō||throw}}. The Latin word {{m|la|adiectivus}} in turn was a calque of {{noncog|grc|ἐπιθετικόν|t=added}}, a derivative of the compound verb {{m|grc|ἐπιτίθημι}}, from which also comes {{m|en|epithet}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈæ.d͡ʒɛk.tɪv/|/ˈæ.d͡ʒɪk.tɪv/|/ˈæ.d͡ʒək.tɪv/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-adjective.ogg|Audio (GA)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
{{wikipedia}}

# {{lb|en|grammar}} A [[word]] that [[modify|modifies]] a [[noun]]  or noun phrase or [[describe]]s a noun’s referent.
#: {{ux|en|The words “big” and “heavy” are English '''adjectives'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1932|year_published=1965|author=Delos W. Lovelace|authorlink=Delos W. Lovelace|title=[[w:King Kong (1933 film)|King Kong]]|page=8|passage="They'll have to invent new '''adjectives''' when I come back. You wait!"}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[dependent]]; an [[accessory]].
#* {{RQ:Fuller Cambridge}}
#*:it must be an '''adjective''' of dain

