===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[make]] an adjective of; to [[form]] or [[convert]] into an adjective.
#* '''1805''', {{w|John Horne Tooke}}, Epea Pteroenta: or The Diversions of Purley Part 2
#*: Language has as much occasion to '''adjective''' the distinct signification of the verb, and to adjective also the mood, as it has to adjective time. It has {{...}} '''adjectived''' all three.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1832|author=William Hunter|title=An Anglo-Saxon grammar, and derivatives|page=46|passage=In English, instead of '''adjectiving''' our own substantives, we have borrowed, in immense numbers, '''adjectived''' signs from other languages{{...}}}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|chiefly as a participle}} To [[characterize]] with an adjective; to [[describe]] by using an adjective.

