===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# of the [[essence]] or essential [[element]] of a thing; as, "substantive information"
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=6 October 2012|magazine=The Economist|url=http://www.economist.com/node/21564222|title=The first presidential debate: Back in the centre, back in the game|passage=In one sense the first debate achieved the worst of all worlds: it managed to be technical, even dull, without being '''substantive''' or especially honest.}}
#: {{syn|en|essential|in essence}}
# having [[substance]]; enduring; solid; firm; substantial
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1836|origyear=1829|title=Literary Remains of the Late William Hazlitt|chapter=Definition of wit|page=19|author={{w|William Hazlitt}}|passage=Once more then, strength and magnitude are qualities which impress the imagination in a powerful and '''substantive''' manner;|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wTbQAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA19}}
#: {{syn|en|meaty|substantial}}
#: {{ant|en|superficial}}
# {{senseid|en|legal rights}}{{lb|en|law}} applying to essential [[legal]] [[principle]]s and [[rule]]s of right; as, "substantive law"
#: {{ant|en|adjective|procedural}}
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} of a [[dye]] that does not need the use of a [[mordant]] to be made [[fast]] to that which is being dyed
#: {{ant|en|adjective}}
# Depending on itself; [[independent]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1765|origyear=1627|author={{w|Francis Bacon}}|chapter=New Atlantis|title=The Works of Francis Bacon|page=356|passage=He therefore taking into consideration, how sufficient and '''substantive''' this land was to maintain itself without any aid at all of the foreigner,|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H3U8VYy7e1YC&pg=PA356}}
# {{lb|en|grammar}} {{clipping of|en|noun substantive}}
#: {{syn|en|substantival}}
# {{lb|en|military|of a rank or appointment}} [[actually]] and [[legally]] held, as distinct from an [[acting]], [[temporary]] or [[honorary]] [[rank]] or [[appointment]]

