{{also|Eagle}}
==English==
[[File:Eagle on roots - crop 3 (430008061).jpg|thumb|An eagle]]
[[File:Eagles in heraldry - collage of arms of Germany Poland Mexico and Egypt.png|thumb|The coats of arms of Germany, Poland, Mexico and Egypt (among others) depict eagles in various colors and styles.]]

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|egle}}, from {{der|en|xno|egle}}, from {{der|en|fro|aigle}}, from {{der|en|la|aquila}}. Displaced native {{cog|enm|earn|ern, earn, arn}}, from {{cog|ang|earn|t=eagle}}. More at {{m|en|erne}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈiːɡəl/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-eagle.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|iːɡəl}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of several large carnivorous and [[carrion]]-eating [[bird]]s in the family [[Accipitridae]], having a powerful [[hooked]] [[bill]] and [[keen]] [[vision]].
#: {{syn|en|erne|broadwing}}
# {{lb|en|US|numismatics|historical}} A [[gold]] [[coin]] with a face value of ten dollars, formerly used in the United States.
# {{lb|en|historical|numismatics}} A 13th-[[century]] [[coin]] [[mint]]ed in [[Europe]] and [[circulate]]d in [[England]] as a [[debase]]d [[sterling]] [[silver]] [[penny]], [[outlaw]]ed under {{w|Edward I of England}}.
# {{lb|en|golf}} A score of [[two]] [[under par]] for a [[hole]].

