===Etymology 3===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|es|ñame}}, substituting ''n'' for the unfamiliar Spanish letter ''ñ''. {{doublet|en|yam}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# Any of several types of [[true yam]] (''[[Dioscorea]]'') used in Caribbean Spanish cooking.

