==English==

===Etymology 1===
[[File:Runic letter fehu.svg|40px|left|Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter ᚠ, which was replaced by Latin ‘f’]] {{inh|en|ang|-}} lower case letter {{m|en|f}}, from 7th century replacement by Latin lower case {{m|la|f}} of the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{m|mul|ᚠ|tr=f||fe}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|en|/ɛf/}}
: {{audio|en|en-us-f.ogg|Audio (US)}}
: {{audio|en|en-uk-f.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|en|/f/}}
* See ''Guide to Pronunciation'', §§ 178, 179, 188, 198, 230 in the 1913 Webster dictionary

====Letter====
{{en-letter|upper=F|lower=f}}

