==Norwegian Nynorsk==

===Etymology===
From {{der|nn|la|famuli}}, from the first word of the fourth line of ''[[w:Ut queant laxis|Ut queant laxis]]'', the medieval hymn on which [[solfège]] was based because its lines started on each note of the scale successively. Through {{bor|nn|it|-}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|nn|/fɑː/}}

===Noun===
{{nn-noun-m1|fa-}}

# {{senseid|nn|solfège}} {{lb|nn|music}} {{l|en|fa|id=solfège}}, a syllable used in [[solfège]] to represent the second note of a [[major scale]].

====Coordinate terms====
* {{sense|scale of solfège}} ''{{l|nn|do|id=solfège}}, {{l|nn|re|id=solfège}}, {{l|nn|mi|id=solfège}}, fa, {{l|nn|sol|id=solfège}} or {{l|nn|so|id=solfège}}, {{l|nn|la|id=solfège}}, {{l|nn|ti|id=solfège}}, {{l|nn|do|id=solfège}}''

===References===
* {{R:The Nynorsk Dictionary}}

