==Old Irish==

===Prefix===
{{sga-infixed pronoun|A}}

# [[him]] {{qualifier|triggers eclipsis}}
# [[it]] {{qualifier|triggers lenition}}

====Usage notes====
This form merges with the prefixes {{m|sga|ro-}}, {{m|sga|no-}}, {{m|sga|di-}}, {{m|sga|to-}}, {{m|sga|fo-}}, {{m|sga|ar-}}, and {{m|sga|imm-}} to form ''ra-'', ''na-'', ''da-'', ''da-'', ''fa-'', ''ara-'', ''imma-'' respectively. It disappears after the particle {{m|sga|ní|t=not}}, its only trace being the mutation it causes (eclipsis in the case of the masculine, lenition in the case of the neuter), thus ''ní cara'' {{gloss|does not love}} vs. ''ní chara'' {{gloss|does not love it}}, ''ní ben'' {{gloss|does not strike}} vs. ''ní mben'' {{gloss|does not strike him}}.

====Derived terms====
{{prefixsee|sga}}

====See also====
{{sga-affixed pronouns}}

