==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|en|aum|awm}}

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|nl|aam}}, from {{der|en|la|ama}}, a variant of {{m|la|hama}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἄμη||bucket}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ɑːm/|/ɔːm/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/ɑm/|/ɔm/}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɑːm|ɔːm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|historical}} A Dutch and German measure of liquids, used in England for [[Rhine]] wine, varying in different cities, being in [[Amsterdam]] about 41 [[wine gallon]]s, in [[Antwerp]] 36½{{,}} and in Hamburg 38¼. {{defdate|first attested around 1350 to 1470}}

