==German==

===Etymology===
From {{der|de|goh|ab}}, from {{der|de|gem-pro|*ab}}. Compare {{cog|en|off-}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Standard German}} {{IPA|de|/ap/|[ʔäpʰ]}}
* {{a|Switzerland}} {{IPA|de|/ab̥/}}
* {{audio|de|De-ab-.ogg|Audio}}

===Prefix===
{{de-pref}}

# {{non-gloss definition|Separable verb prefix that indicates removal or quitting, [[off]], [[away]].}}
#: {{prefixusex|de|fahren|gloss1=to drive|abfahren|gloss2=to depart, drive away}}
#: {{prefixusex|de|spülen|gloss1=to rinse, wash|abspülen|gloss2=to rinse off, wash off}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Separable verb prefix that indicates a downward movement, [[down]].}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Separable verb prefix that indicates [[from]] or [[of]].}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Noun prefix that indicates [[deviation]] or being different from the source.}}
#: {{prefixusex|de|Art|gloss1=kind, sort|Abart|gloss2=variety, variant, anomality}}
#: {{prefixusex|de|Gott|gloss1=God|Abgott|gloss2=idol; god other than the true God}}
#: {{prefixusex|de|Laut|gloss1=sound|Ablaut|gloss2=[[ablaut]]; vowel gradation or alternation}}

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|off}} {{l|de|aus-}}
* {{sense|down}} {{l|de|hinab-}}, {{l|de|herab-}}, {{l|de|runter-}}, {{l|de|herunter-}}, {{l|de|hinunter-}}

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|on}} {{l|de|an-}}
* {{sense|up}} {{l|de|auf-}}, {{l|de|rauf-}}, {{l|de|hinauf-}}, {{l|de|herauf-}}

