===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|en|abacá|abáca|abaka|abaká}}

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|es|abacá}}, from the {{der|en|tl|-}} name for the plant, {{m|tl|abaka|abaká}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˌæb.əˈkɑ/}}
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|en|/ˌæb.əˈkɑ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{taxlink|Musa textilis|species|noshow=1|ver=161026}}, a species of [[banana]] tree native to the [[Philippines]] grown for its textile, rope- and [[papermaking]] fibre. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=2}}</ref>
#: {{syn|en|Manila Hemp|Manilla hemp|textile banana}}
